10,36,30,29]} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. e5 Nfd7 5. f4 c5 6. Nf3 a6 ({
I think} 6... Qb6 7. Be3 {is going to be just a transposition. Black can
rather choose} a6 ({or} 7... Nc6)) 7. Be3 Qb6 8. a3 $5 {I like this modest
calm move} ({Another option is} 8. Na4 Qa5+ 9. c3 cxd4 10. b4 Qc7 11. Qxd4 Nc6
12. Qd2 b5 13. Nb2 $13 {Keeping more pieces on the board. But here Black has a
nice pawn structure and knight on b2 is a bit misplayed}) 8... Nc6 ({The idea} 
