side with two bishops more. After} 12... f6 13. exf6 Nxf6 14. Bd3 Ng4 15. Bd2
e5 16. c4 $1 {The complications look in White's favour} Qxd1+ 17. Rxd1 e4 18.
cxd5 exd3 19. dxc6 bxc6 20. O-O O-O 21. h3 Nf6 22. Ne5 {and White wins a pawn
with a good chance to convert this advantage in the endgame.}) (12... Qa5+ 13.
Qd2 Qxd2+ 14. Kxd2 {Without queens White's advantage is quite obvious. Black
has no air for his pieces. The only pawn break is f7-f6 which opens the
position in White's favour} f6 15. exf6 Nxf6 16. Bd3 {1-0 (49) Inarkiev,E 
(2689)-Mohr, G (2473) Katowice POL 2017}) 13. c4 {White opens the centre and
Black is more or less forced to exchange the queens which leads to a
favourable endgame for White after:} ({Now} 13. Bd3 $6 {is not so good because
