27. Rxb7 Rxe5+ 28. Kd2 Rxg5 29. Bxa6 Ra5 30. Bb5 e5 31. Bxd7 exd4 32. Be8 Rxa3
33. Bxf7+ Kh8 34. Bb3 Nd7 35. Bc2 d3 36. Rxd7 dxc2 {1/2 (44) Heimann, A (2528)
-Stojanovic,M (2511) Switzerland 2018}) (18. Nd4 Rd7 $1 {Again our typical
maneuver} 19. Nb3 Rc7 20. Bf2 dxc4 21. Bxc4 Bd7 22. Na5 Bb5 $1 (22... Rb8 {
It is the safer choice, but I prefer the text move.}) 23. Rhc1 (23. Bxb5 Nd5+
24. Kd2 axb5 25. Rxb5 {A nice positional pawn sacrifice. The engine first
screams that White is better, but then realizes that Black is more than OK in
