Qxf4+ 37. Ke2 (37. Kg1 e3 $1 38. Qe1 Kf7 39. Rxc6 Qg4+ 40. Qg3 Qd1+ 41. Kg2
Qe2+ $11) 37... Qxh2+ 38. Ke3 (38. Kd1 Ba4+ {That's why White should play 35.
b5 first} 39. Kc1 e3) 38... Qg1+ 39. Kd2 Ba4 {and White cannot avoid the
perpetual check.}) 36. Qd4 $1 {Finally taking everything under control} Qh5 37.
Kg1 Qf3 38. Rd8+ Kg7 39. Qf2 Qg4 40. Rd6 e3 41. Qxe3 {1-0 Ponomariov-Bluebaum,
Doha, 2015} *

